<h1>Problem 796 - 2021 EGMO, P5 of 6, CG</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>A plane has a special point \(O\) called the origin. Let \(P\) be a set of 2021 points in the plane such that
<ul><li>no three points in \(P\) lie on a line and</li><li>no two points in \(P\) lie on a line through the origin.</li></ul>
A triangle with vertices in \(P\) is fat if \(O\) is strictly inside the triangle. Find the maximum number of fat triangles.</p>
